This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it presents a new mathematical model to evaluate the accuracy of time series classification algorithms. It may also belong to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with anomaly detection, which is a common application of AI. Additionally, it may be relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) as it proposes a new model for evaluating the performance of time series classification algorithms. It may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cryptography (cs.CR) and computer vision (cs.CV) as these fields often deal with time series data and may benefit from improved precision and recall metrics.
